Kata Containers: add TPM socket support for Cloud Hypervisor

Pod annotation io.katacontainers.config.hypervisor.tpm_socket passes
a host-side swtpm socket path to CLH, which exposes a TPM 2.0 CRB
device to the guest VM.

--- a/virtcontainers/hypervisor.go
+++ b/virtcontainers/hypervisor.go
@@ -558,6 +558,9 @@
 	// GuestHookPath is the path within the VM that will be used for 'drop-in' hooks
 	GuestHookPath string

+	// TpmSocket is the path to the swtpm socket for vTPM device passthrough via CLH
+	TpmSocket string
+
 	// VMid is the id of the VM that create the hypervisor if the VM is created by the factory.
 	// VMid is "" if the hypervisor is not created by the factory.
 	VMid string

